Clock Properties
       child_clocks
              Returns the first level of generated clocks. This property  also
              works for nested generated clocks.

              Return type: collection

       comment
              Returns the comment set for the specified clock.

              Return Type: String

              For example,

              get_property [get_clocks CK] comment

       clock_network_pins
              Returns  a  collection  of all pins on the clock network for the
              clock.

              Return type: collection

       delay_max_fall
              Returns the maximum falling delay value for the clock.

              Return type: float

       delay_max_rise
              Returns the maximum rising delay value for the clock.

              Return type: float

       delay_min_fall
              Returns the minimum falling delay value for the clock.

              Return type: float

       delay_min_rise
              Returns the minimum rising delay value for the clock.

              Return type: float

       divide_by
              Returns dfactor set for the specified clock.

              For example,

              get_property [get_clocks ck] divide_by

              Return Type: Integer

       driving_network_pins
              Returns a collection of the network pins of the driving clock.

              For example,

              get_property [get_clocks clk] driving_network_pins

              Return Type: Collection

       duty_cycle
              Returns the duty cycle for the specified clock.

              For example,

              get_property [get_clocks CLK] duty_cycle

              Return Type: Float

       edges  Return the edges that are set for a specified clock.

              For example,

              get_property [get_clocks ck] edges

              Return Type: String

       edge_shift
              Return the edge shift that is set for a specified clock.

              For example,

              get_property [get_clocks ck] edge_shift

              Return Type: String

       generated_clocks_extended
              Returns generated clocks derived from the regular clock.

              Return type: collection

       hierarchical_name
              Returns the complete hierarchical name of the clock.

              Return type: string

       hold_uncertainty
              Returns the most conservative uncertainty of  all  the  possible
              uncertainty   assertions   associated   with  a  pin,  when  the
              set_clock_uncertainty -hold parameter is specified.

              For example,

              get_property [get_clocks <clock name>] hold_uncertainty

              Return Type: Float

       is_context_mapped
              Returns a value of true if a clock is mapped to  the  top  in  a
              context.  Additionally,  this  is  also  reported  with  the re-
              port_clocks command.

              For example,

              get_property [get_clocks <clock name>] is_context_mapped

              Return Type: Boolean

       ideal_transition_max_fall
              Returns the ideal clock transition asserted on  clock  waveforms
              specified  with the set_clock_transition command using the -fall
              and -max parameters.

              Return type: float

       ideal_transition_max_rise
              Returns the ideal clock transition asserted on  clock  waveforms
              specified  with the set_clock_transition command using the -rise
              and -max parameters.

              Return type: float

       ideal_transition_min_fall
