Timing Path Properties
       applied_exception_type
              Returns the type of applied exceptions for a timing  path.  This
              property can be used to query dominant timing exceptions affect-
              ing  a  timing  path. You can use this property to query on con-
              strained/unconstrained timing paths.

              The possible return values are  -  multi_cycle,  path_delay  and
              false_path  -  indicating multicycle path, minimum/maximum delay
              path, and timing false path, respectively. The software will re-
              turn one of these values for pin-based timing  exceptions.  How-
              ever, the software returns "NA" when false paths are defined for
              clock  objects,  or  if the paths do not have any related timing
              exception.

              Return Type: String

